It's perhaps not too surprising that the most popular one was <hymn>I'm a Pioneer Too (#1034)</hymn>. This batch was released just before [Pioneer Day](/posts/pioneer_day) in Utah, so it temporarily enjoys its spot in first place. After a few weeks though, I think we'll see it sink lower because I don't think too many wards will be singing it "off-season."


## What hymns are most popular each week?

It's been long enough that we can get an idea of which hymns were popular when. The following plot shows the percentage of wards that sang each hymn *of the wards that sang any fourth batch hymns*. 



::: {.cell .column-page}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){width=1248}
:::
:::



The most obvious trend is that <hymn>I'm a Pioneer Too (#1034)</hymn> saw a big spike at the end of July, which is the Sunday before Pioneer Day here in Utah. On July 20th, half of wards that sang from the fourth batch sang that hymn that day.


## When during meetings are these hymns sung?

We can also see when during sacrament meetings these hymns have been sung. Data sparsity makes this a pretty unreliable table though. We'll have to wait a few more weeks or months to really see some more meaningful trends.



